    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-08T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-08T16:00:00-05:00" n="5"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d5">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/769</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-08T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 8, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your cipher telegram of December 6, 7 p.m. The American Government supports the
                    view that China is entirely within her right in employing troops to protect her
                    sovereignty and territorial integrity. This Government would not, however, be
                    disposed to encourage an armed conflict.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
